  "course_description": "Epidemiologic methods are covered for studying the determinants and distributions of health outcomes in human population with an emphasis on hypothesis formulation; causal inference; experimental vs. observational research; measurement; detection of interaction; study design (e.g. cohort, cross-sectional, case-control); evaluation of the sources and direction of bias; control of confounding factors; random error (frequentist vs. Bayesian approach); and epidemiology in clinical settings (screening, diagnosis, and therapy).",
